Ljungberg on the performance: &ldquo;I was very happy. We had a very young side out there because I wanted energy &amp; I wanted to give them chances. We dominated possession &amp; chances &amp; you could see Everton getting tired &amp; frustrated.&rdquo; #afc<br />
<br />
Ljungberg: &ldquo;I thought we could have won the game with the chances we had, but I loved the spirit we saw &amp; that&rsquo;s what you need in the Premier League. I wanted to see people that would run &amp; fight for the team. We can&rsquo;t rely on our name, we have to fight &amp; do the dirty things.&rdquo;

